For different treatments for my health, I lived in Florida (Tampa/Clearwater Beach Area) and in Los Angeles. I loved living in such different cities, it inspires me and I learned a lot from it. 
I'm also graduated as a Nutritionist, so my passions really are Fashion, Beauty and Health. I'm now back in the Netherlands, and I'm pregnant with our first child!

bio:
My name is Sunny Gu, a Los Angeles-based fashion & beauty illustrator. 

I have been commissioned by the likes of Condé Nast, Vogue Magazine, Teen Vogue, ELLE Magazine , InStyle, Bloomingdales, Macy's, Nordstrom, Versace, Dolce & Gabbana's Swide Magazine, Carolina Herrera, Brian Atwood, Express, South Coast Plaza, Beverly Center,The Grove, La Prairie, Shiseido, FANCL , Neutrogena and HBO among others. 

I was born and raised in China, I moved to the United States when I was 13. After encountering people from different backgrounds, I became very curious about other cultures. I learned to observe and discover beauties in everything around me. 

I wish to find a way to capture and preserve the beauties that I see, the kindness that I feel, and recreate them in someway. I decided to become an illustrator and artist. 

For most of my illustrations, I paint them in watercolor. I love the vibrancy and unpredictable nature of watercolor. Occasionally I use graphite or acrylic paint to render some special textures. I also create digital art for surface design and textiles. 

My illustrations are always full of vibrant colors, rich details and delightful feelings. My work, on the other hand, is an endless journey searching for beauty, value, truth and self. When I paint, I am bathed in happiness, I hope my colorful illustrations can bring you some joy too! 

Wish you a wonderful day! 

Sunny

bio:
Tuesday vintage is an online creative platform where founder and stylist, Rachel March showcases the innovative work of herself and other creatives alike whilst also doubling as a store selling unique fashion forward vintage pieces.

Rachel’s extensive set of skills in styling are now being used to collaborate with the many artists in this world where they will then be featured on the blog, exposing viewers to upcoming trends and talent to keep an eye on. 

The store heavily relies on trend forecasts where the seasonal vintage buys reflect up to date fashion movements whilst remaining unique and one of a kind. 
Rachel’s coordination with designers, labels, style icons, photographers, bloggers and PR companies across the globe ensures that the shop will forever offer eccentric pieces like no other and the Tuesday Vintage platform will constantly be showcasing the best of the best. 

Much like most age old tales - there is a beginning, a middle and an end. 
For Tuesday Vintage, this is only the beginning. 

Thankful to everyone who has joined this wild adventure, Rachel truly believes it's all of the people she has met along the way that keeps this inspiration and magic growing.. ♡

name: Lindsi Lane•So|Lindsi
bio:
Lindsi Lane is on a mission to prove that with the right outfit, a good attitude and a sense of humor, anything is possible. The New York City-based writer is the founder of lifestyle website, SoLindsi.com, a carefully curated edit of personal stories, satirical commentary, and outfit inspiration. Lindsi draws upon her fashion background and straight-shooting persona to create Humor with a Sense of Style. 

The Indiana University-grad began her fashion career working for Gucci, Michael Kors, and Elle magazine, before becoming the youngest personal shopper in Barney’s New York history at age 23. She went on to form styling company, Lindsi Michelle Lane LLC, and was signed as the first ‘By Appointment’ stylist for Ford Artists NYC. Despite her successful styling career, Lindsi was eager to show others that personal style extends far beyond the clothing on your back. 

In 2015, she launched SoLindsi.com to connect with readers as a digital hybrid of their best friend and stylist. “Style is how you paint your blank canvas, but your voice is the essence of your personal style,” says Lindsi, who empowers readers with her quick-witted charm and honest content – think Sex and the City meets Amy Schumer. “My mission is to inspire people to be comfortable in their own skin, embrace who they are beyond the surface, and laugh along the way.” 

SoLindsi.com is a lifestyle website best known for its Humor with a Sense of Style. bio:
Garrin Evan is a Fort Lauderdale-based fashion and beauty photographer, specializing in location-based advertising, public relations and editorial photography. An avowed colorist, Evan’s work features vibrant splashes of color, as well as eye-catching geometric compositions. He is drawn to the elegant, mysterious, sensual and confident. His clients include advertising and public relations agencies, magazines and consumer brands. 

Evan’s photography has been influenced by a life of artistic endeavors. In the 1990s, he worked in marketing and promotion for Atlantic Records, promoting acts like Stone Temple Pilots, Collective Soul, Tori Amos, Juliana Hatfield and Hootie & the Blowfish. Evan is also an accomplished artist and self-taught painter. A decade studying figure drawing helped him develop his eye for fashion photography. 

A guiding philosophy to his work: Create a fun, friendly and professional environment and let creativity flourish. Evan prefers shooting on location in urban or natural spaces, and through effective planning and clear direction, he creates imagery that tells a unique story. He has photographed Miss Universe, a swimsuit calendar for the NHL Florida Panthers, and a United States Presidential Candidate.

Passionate, creative and curious, Chef Kara Quick will bring the meaning of flavour into your life. Starting in her home kitchen at the age of 12, she continues to learn, grow and execute her belief that food is life. Kara attended a small culinary program, taught by former CIA and Johnson and Wales graduates, and began working in fine dining kitchens, as well as yacht provisions, off premise catering, private luxury events, as well as Festival and Concession work. I love working with fine foods, all cuisines and always am willing to try! name: Progressive Traveller
bio:
Hi, I’m Donna, the Progressive Traveller who has been travelling extensively since 2001.  

When I am not travelling the world, I make my home in Tumbulgum, Northern NSW Australia. Tumbulgum is an exquisite, small riverside village located at the confluence of the Rivers Rous and Tweed overlooked by the iconic and majestic Wollumbin Mount Warning and surrounding Border Ranges. 

Although, I have lived most of my life in major cities, I fell in love with the Northern Rivers in the early 80s and moved there in 2012. 

One of the things, I most love about living there is how close I am to the river, mountains, national parks, golden sandy beaches, regional towns and beautiful Brisbane is only a short 90-minute drive away. 

Travelling the world is my passion and obsession. I am continuously researching, taking notes and planning the next trip. For me, travel enhances our lives and relationships. Travel excites us, educates us about how others live, it helps us to understand other peoples cultures and point of view, it can also make us grateful and more appreciative of our own lives. 

There’s something utterly addictive about travel. It’s not called the travel ‘bug’ for nothing. Travel can infect you for life! The more places I travel, the more destinations I want to discover. Each place I’ve visited has left me with great memories of the architecture, scenery, food, culture and people. 

Experiencing new cultures, devouring different cuisines and meeting new friends along the way is just part of the fasinating journey of travel. 

Progressive Traveller is a travel blog created to connect people with places all around the world. To inspire others to EXPLORE and LIVE life to the full. It’s my desire to connect with others in the travel industry and build a success business in the field that I love and excites me.  

Safe travels      
Enjoy every minute…….like it is your last! 

Happy Days, Donna

bio:
Lowkita is a rising Canadian female hip-hop artist & blogger with grand intent and the passion to back it up. 
Lowkita literally translates as “crazy girl” in Spanish and this artist lives the definition; her sound is an infusion of classic hip-hop B-girl sass with organic raw rhythm, and her demanding stage presence will draw the attention of any crowd. 
Following her natural passion for rhythm and arts, Lowkita enrolled in her first ballet lesson when she was only 4 years old, and continually developed and re-shaped that passion, expanding into jazz and funk lessons at age 8 and forming collective dance groups in her early teens. All of this progression naturally led towards the realm of hip-hop and Dancehall, it wasn’t long before Lowkita found a new form of expression. 
Growing up in the gangster rap and rhythm & blues era of the 90′s, Lowkita was influenced by the work of successful artists like Kriss Kross and Brandy, but it was actually the ageless art of poetics that lead her into rhythmical lyricism. At 15, Lowkita developed a friendship with a young aspiring poet who would share her verses with Lowkita. Given her musical influences, Lowkita wished to match the conversational power of the monologues with the complimenting backdrop of powerful songs, so she would recite her friend’s words like a dance, matching the movement and tones of the words with those of the instruments, which effectively marked the beginning of her hip-hop artistry. 
Lowkita has been developing her talents ever since a young and has been able to create a following for herself In Calgary and most recently, Vancouver. Her drive and work ethic sets her apart from other acts her age, and her goals and passions have led her to Montreal where she attended Radio school and back to Vancouver where she attended John Casablanca for Fashion Business stage is her true passion though, and she prides herself on finishing she put her mind to. 
Her sound is best described as powerful, rhythmic, and dynamic: her syllables jump with a melodic precision and boldness and her attitude allows her to jump out of even the most minimal of beats. Lowkita has been developing the B-girl rhythm rap for years, and the timing could not have been better: commercially successful acts like NiCKI Minaj, and Halifax’s Kay have opened the public door for hard-hitting female lyricism, and Lowkita has the youth and passion to excel in this highly sought-after genre. 
Lowkita has now recently joint forces with Emotions open mic to bring her music and talent to the next level. With Mr Floetic, A local Vancouver producer and DJ, along with the rest of the Emotions team Lowkita is ready to bring something new and represent no only Canada but her own Caribbean culture as well.

Noelia Lorenzo Monge born in San Juan, Puerto Rico and raised in Miami, Florida), mostly known as Noelia, is a Puerto Rican pop singer who rose to fame in 1999. Her self-titled debut album was certified as a gold album in the United States. During her career she has had 10 Latin Billboard Top 40 hits in Spanish, 5 Club Dance Top 40 Hits in English and has eighteen worldwide gold and nine worldwide multi-platinum -certified albums, along with one RIAA-certified Gold (500,000) record in the United States. 

Noelia has sold more than 10 million Albums worldwide, won multiple awards, and has won Latin Billboard’s Award Album of the year as well. She has crossed borders to Europe to be acknowledged as the “International Singer of the Year” in Italy, at the prestigious Festival Bar. Her record, “40 Grados” (Forty Degrees), was infused with the myriad of mixed feelings that invaded Noelia with her auspicious return to the world of music and granted many awards again in 2007. 

The single “Cómo Duele” (How does it hurt), quickly climbed last year 2007 to the first top ten in popularity on the radio in the United States, according to Billboard Magazine, and during 38 consecutive weeks was perched among the Top 20 of Latin pop, also according to that prestigious international music publication, she was also nominated again in 2007 to the Latin Billboard Awards for the third time . 

The single, “Tú” (You), was awarded “Song of the Year” and Album of the Year by Billboard, projecting her image speedily, towards Spain , Italy and Grece. And so she infused the Iberian peninsula, with the contagious rhythms of her “Candela” (Hot Stuff), which was then named “The Song of the Summer.” 

Several Magazine’s covers have Feature Noelia, such as: People en Espanol, Maxim Espanol USA, Maxim Mexico, H for Man. The prestigious People Magazine en Espanol has named Noelia on of the most beautiful 50 people in the Latin Music Industry. She also was Fetatured on the Playboy Cover of their International Edition in 2010 supporting the Fight Against Breast Cancer , Pink Cover of Playboy with Noelia. ( Not available in the U.S.) Mexico and other countries only… 

In 2009 Actress and Top Model Elisabetta Canalis released in Italy a compilation Album called “TOP HITS by Hollywood-Milano” 2009 (Sony-BMG) this album inlcluded the most sucessful singers from America in Europe, Inlcuding Noelia’s Caribbean Queen Reloaded Version, Katy Perry, Pink, Lady Gaga, The compilation was awarded with Platinum status on the first week of sales. 

By mid 2011 Noelia have made history on the Hispanic Market in the United States by breaking a record for online audience with her intimate online Concert produced by Hispanic Media Giant Univision, the concert achieved more than 3.5 million Viewers. It is a record with no precedent in History of Hispanic or Spanish online events. 

In April 2012 Noelia makes a Historic Double Hot shoot Debut in The Same Week at The Billboard Charts (Dance) and (Latin Hot Track) with her Hit Single song “Kiss Me”. 

The Song ” Kiss Me” consolidates Noelia in the American Dance Billboard Charts Reaching number 14 on the Chart. 

In August 2012 Noelia gets ready to launch her first Full English Single for the Mainstream Market, produced by Music Legend TIMBALAND who’s production for International Music Stars like Madona , Justin Timaberlake , and many more making him one of the Most Powerful Producers of the world. 


Noelia Releases ” My Everything” to U.S. and European Market, making a Gigantic splash debut on the Billboard Dance Charts and the U.K Charts. In the last week of August Noelia made a debut on the Billboard Charts on the Spot 49 while Mariah Carey with a big publicized return does it at the Position number 42 on the Charts. 
By the First week of September Noelia position her self in the Top 20, and brining awareness to world media that a new International music sensation is rising. 

During the 2012 Olympics Games, The Russian Team of Rhythm Gymnastics makes a superb demonstration at the Rhythm of Noelia”s international hit ” Candela” remixed by Noelia and given to the Russian Team for their Gold Medal Winning Performance. 

During September and October 2012 Noelia stormed the Billboard Dance Charts and with 11 weeks at the Top 20 , by November 10 Billboard had reported Noelia at Number 2 for second consecutive weeks. Making “My Everything” one of the Most Successful Club songs in the World for 2012.

bio:
Ben Miller may be a native Californian with a sunny disposition and debonair charm, but his photography and directing career has taken him around the world, from Rio de Janeiro to London, Vancouver to Seoul. 

As a former US diplomat and graduate of UC Berkeley, Ben spent years developing the left half of his brain, but can’t help but be repeatedly pulled back to the right. 

His current work focuses on bringing out true emotions from people of all walks of life, from global celebrities at the academy awards to homeless living in the desert. Whether shooting a personal project or doing work for top brands and magazines, Ben brings an optimistically authentic eye to each project. He delights in the strange and the mundane, and the intersection of the two.

bio:
I love my family, friends. I wouldn't be in the position I am in without their support. I'm super humble and open to learn new things. 

My life currently revolves around school and Cheerleading. I'm a full time student at Trinity Valley Community College in Athens, Tx. I'm on a full scholarship for cheerleading. 
I attended Jefferson Community College in Louisville, KY 2014-2015, which is affiliated with the University of Louisville. I also cheered there winning College nationals. 
I'm a 2014 and 2017 Nfinity Legend. 
It's basically a contest to see who the best cheerleaders are. Everyone from across the United States sends in a video of their skills to Nfinity (amazing cheer business) they only choose the top 50 cheerleaders and I was chosen! 
Before cheer I was a gymnast for five years. I'm VERY athletic and I'm determined to succeed at any challenge/opportunity. 

My followers came from Vine. I had 400k followers before vine shut down. Most of my followers followed my other social media. My videos consisted of dancing, being silly and tumbling/stunting videos. I've been off of social media lately so my followers have been disappearing. But my best friend and I recently started a YouTube channel! 

My crowd mainly consists of females and male cheerleaders. Athletes. And anyone who enjoys my posts. 

I love taking pictures, promoting products, talking with people and exploring my surroundings. I'm HIGHLY out going. Making people smile is one of my hidden talents!
